00:06:41.766 --> 00:06:42.996
people to focus on what they

00:06:42.996 --> 00:06:44.416
need, which is to find

00:06:44.416 --> 00:06:47.336
something, to ask a question, to

00:06:47.336 --> 00:06:48.056
get their bearings.

00:06:48.946 --> 00:06:52.936
And it's amazing how much an

00:06:52.936 --> 00:06:54.866
experience can change when

00:06:54.866 --> 00:06:56.756
actions are removed from the UI.

00:06:56.756 --> 00:06:58.986
So I want to show you another

00:06:58.986 --> 00:06:59.656
example.

00:07:00.416 --> 00:07:02.056
This is an app called Vanido.

00:07:02.476 --> 00:07:03.876
It helps you learn how to sing.

00:07:05.116 --> 00:07:06.626
So if you're the kind of person

00:07:06.856 --> 00:07:08.366
who wants to learn how to sing

00:07:08.956 --> 00:07:11.426
with literally no one hearing

00:07:11.426 --> 00:07:13.696
your or judging you, this app is

00:07:13.696 --> 00:07:14.246
amazing.

00:07:15.196 --> 00:07:16.336
This is the UI.

00:07:17.166 --> 00:07:18.396
It's so simple.

00:07:19.066 --> 00:07:20.576
The app tracks the pitch of my

00:07:20.576 --> 00:07:22.836
voice while I'm singing and it's

00:07:22.836 --> 00:07:24.596
continually giving me feedback.

00:07:24.736 --> 00:07:26.606
Am I hitting my notes or not?

00:07:27.876 --> 00:07:28.906
So let me show you.

00:07:29.516 --> 00:07:33.056
[ Laughter ]

00:07:33.556 --> 00:07:35.066
I'm actually not going to do a

00:07:35.066 --> 00:07:35.706
live demo.

00:07:36.241 --> 00:07:38.241
[ Laughter ]

00:07:38.466 --> 00:07:39.836
But I am going to sing along

00:07:40.301 --> 00:07:42.301
[harmonica note]

00:07:42.586 --> 00:07:45.536
