00:07:45.536 --> 00:07:48.476
I want you to see how it works.

00:07:50.516 --> 00:07:57.516
[ Music ]

00:07:58.516 --> 00:08:06.126
[ Cheering ]

00:08:06.626 --> 00:08:08.856
You can leave feedback in my

00:08:09.086 --> 00:08:09.526
session.

00:08:10.131 --> 00:08:12.131
[ Laughter ]

00:08:12.246 --> 00:08:14.076
So what I love about Vanido is

00:08:14.116 --> 00:08:16.376
that it has stripped away what

00:08:16.376 --> 00:08:18.606
music education looks like,

00:08:18.606 --> 00:08:18.846
right?

00:08:18.846 --> 00:08:20.326
There's no charts or notes.

00:08:20.396 --> 00:08:22.666
It's colorful, it's animated,

00:08:22.666 --> 00:08:23.496
and it's fun.

00:08:24.376 --> 00:08:25.766
And you should have heard me

00:08:25.766 --> 00:08:27.866
sing before I started using this

00:08:27.866 --> 00:08:28.086
app.

00:08:28.416 --> 00:08:29.356
It really works.

00:08:29.786 --> 00:08:31.806
And there's only one interactive

00:08:31.806 --> 00:08:33.046
element on the screen when

00:08:33.046 --> 00:08:34.256
you're singing and it's way up

00:08:34.256 --> 00:08:35.826
at the top left.

00:08:36.676 --> 00:08:38.506
So you can hold your phone like

00:08:38.506 --> 00:08:40.336
a microphone and really belt it

00:08:40.336 --> 00:08:42.666
out without worrying about

00:08:42.666 --> 00:08:44.096
accidentally exiting your

00:08:44.096 --> 00:08:44.576
lesson.

00:08:47.066 --> 00:08:47.756
So this is radical

00:08:47.756 --> 00:08:49.656
simplification and that's what I

00:08:49.656 --> 00:08:50.516
mean, that's the first

00:08:50.516 --> 00:08:52.736
manifestation of intent and

00:08:52.836 --> 00:08:54.116
intentional design.

00:08:55.656 --> 00:08:57.396
Being radical means taking

00:08:57.396 --> 00:08:58.906
risks, right?

00:08:58.906 --> 00:09:00.266
Removing a bunch of stuff from

00:09:00.266 --> 00:09:02.116
the UI could be jarring if you

00:09:02.116 --> 00:09:02.906
don't do it right.

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:04.286
But I think there's a way to

00:09:04.286 --> 00:09:05.276
reduce your risk.

00:09:05.486 --> 00:09:07.356
So next I want to talk about

00:09:07.356 --> 00:09:09.786
people and about orienting your

00:09:09.786 --> 00:09:12.306
design around what people really

00:09:12.306 --> 00:09:12.716
want.

00:09:13.206 --> 00:09:14.426
So what do they want?

00:09:14.876 --> 00:09:16.466
I think this is worth exploring

00:09:16.816 --> 00:09:17.756
because it's almost never

00:09:17.756 --> 00:09:18.426
obvious.

00:09:20.036 --> 00:09:22.536
The first needs that you see

00:09:22.536 --> 00:09:24.156
when you start kind of looking

00:09:24.286 --> 00:09:27.206
at people and the users that you

00:09:27.206 --> 00:09:28.806
might want to serve are

00:09:28.806 --> 00:09:30.476
superficial and you need to dig

00:09:30.476 --> 00:09:31.436
past those.

00:09:31.986 --> 00:09:33.206
They might be the first ones

00:09:33.206 --> 00:09:34.616
that you think about addressing

00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:35.776
or they might be the ones that

00:09:35.776 --> 00:09:37.406
pulled you into the problem in

00:09:37.406 --> 00:09:39.876
the first place, but you need to

00:09:39.876 --> 00:09:42.516
keep digging because those

00:09:42.616 --> 00:09:45.096
superficial needs often mask

00:09:45.556 --> 00:09:46.946
deeper needs, right, you could

00:09:46.946 --> 00:09:48.646
solve them but not really solve

00:09:48.646 --> 00:09:50.396
the persons' problem.

00:09:50.676 --> 00:09:52.556
So you have to keep digging.

00:09:53.146 --> 00:09:54.516
The second element of

00:09:54.516 --> 00:09:55.786
intentional design that I want

00:09:55.786 --> 00:09:57.546
to get into here is called deep

00:09:57.546 --> 00:09:58.506
understanding.

00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:00.046
So knowing the person that you

00:10:00.046 --> 00:10:01.706
want to reach and the actually

00:10:01.706 --> 00:10:02.796
problem that they have.

00:10:03.556 --> 00:10:05.726
The deeper you dig the more

00:10:05.726 --> 00:10:07.386
likely you are to see where the

00:10:07.486 --> 00:10:09.616
real opportunity to meet their

00:10:09.616 --> 00:10:10.406
needs is.

00:10:10.696 --> 00:10:12.196
And the app that really shows

00:10:12.196 --> 00:10:14.066
this off, in my opinion, is

00:10:14.066 --> 00:10:15.296
called Streaks Workout.

00:10:16.216 --> 00:10:17.916
So it's a workout app but I want

00:10:17.916 --> 00:10:19.076
to go behind the scenes a little

00:10:19.076 --> 00:10:19.306
bit.

00:10:20.016 --> 00:10:22.176
On the surface it looks like

00:10:22.176 --> 00:10:23.266
many workout apps.

00:10:23.266 --> 00:10:24.536
